I‚Äôm glad I found an experienced dentist who was able to identify my oral issues when many others couldn‚Äôt. Whenever I went for scaling and polishing, most dentists would tell me my teeth were very clean. Such comments felt like a taboo to me because there are always hidden or hard-to-reach areas that a toothbrush can't properly clean.
Today, my teeth feel incredibly clean. Before starting the procedure, Dr. Ng mentioned that her scaling might be more painful compared to other dentists. She repeatedly confirmed that I was okay with it before proceeding. Her treatment focused not on surface cleaning but on deep cleaning.
It‚Äôs rare to find such a dentist nowadays because many people are afraid of pain, so most dentists choose to focus only on surface cleaning to minimize discomfort. This approach is highly personal. If you value deep cleaning, Dr. Ng is absolutely the right choice. However, if you are pain sensitive, I wouldn‚Äôt recommend visiting her, as your gums may need 2-3 days to recover after the procedure.

reviews.text:
Made an appointment for scaling and polishing at RM99, WhatsApp booking was easy, responsive and fuss free (I even managed to get an appointment slot for the same day). The clinic is very nicely done up, feels relaxing sitting and waiting for my turn and I didn‚Äôt have to wait long after the registration process to be called into the treatment room.

Dr Yew was assigned to me and her services were excellent. She was warm and inviting (I somehow always have this terrible fear of dentists) and that helped a lot with my anxiety. She then proceeded to do a check of my teeth and found that two fillings were worn out and showed some signs of initial decay, taking photos of the affected areas and spending the time and effort to explain the situation. During the treatment she constantly checked in if I was ok, and was very understanding towards my fears / low pain threshold.

In the end, I spent a total of RM439 on two posterior tooth fillings (RM140 each), a scaling and polishing (RM99 as advertised) and an air polishing (RM60) as I had dark tea stains in between teeth that normal polishing were unable to remove. Dr Yew also showed me the after photos of my teeth and I was pleasantly surprised with the results. Would recommend this dental clinic to anyone looking for affordable yet professional dental services - personally I will also be back.
